This film holds a really special place in my heart. 10 years ago a group of talented people came together to tell this story about a flawed kid from Queens who wants to bring his family together before getting locked up. As I've gotten older, I've realized how important it is to keep family ties strong. But with current technology, it seems to have pushed us further away, isolating and dividing us. The themes of gentrification and institutional effects on individuals are still very relevant, but it's how these characters navigate their circumstances that sticks. It's a testament to the wonderful cast and crew we had that makes this story timeless (save for a few flip phones and CD's here and there). It's been a long time coming but I'm very proud to announce that "Inside A Change" the 2019 remastered director's cut is now streaming only on Amazon Prime. Whether you remember this film in theaters a decade ago or streaming it now from the comfort of your home, just know it was made with a lot of love from a truly diverse group of filmmakers. Oh yeah and please leave us a review. :)

So long old friend. Since 2004 you've been a major part of my life. Getting me where I needed to go with no complaints. You've been on every video shoot, every family moment, every journey. From the streets of NYC to the trails in MI. So happy you got to see us find a new home in A2 and make new friends along the way. I don't know why I'm crying over a car. I suppose it's because you were more than that to us. You are our family and hopefully you can bring new memories for someone else. Thanks Chitty... ❤️ always - Rik, Nancy, Chloe, Fifi
